<p><b>Industrial and Organizational Psychology</b> (also known as <i>I/O psychology</i>, <i>work psychology</i>, <i>work and organizational psychology</i>, <i>occupational psychology</i>, <i>personnel psychology</i> or <i>talent assessment</i>) applies psychology to organizations and the workplace. "Industrial-organizational psychologists contribute to an organization's success by improving the performance and well-being of its people. An I-O psychologist researches and identifies how behaviors and attitudes can be improved through hiring practices, training programs, and feedback systems."<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><br /></p>
